OL,3,C23 people die from drug misuse in the
OL,4,Csouth of Scotland as national numbers
OL,5,Crise
OL,7,FFigures released on Tuesday show that
OL,8,Fthe number of people in Scotland who
OL,9,Fdied due to drug misuse in 2023
OL,10,Fincreased by 12% compared to 2022.
OL,12,FSome 1,172 people died last year, 151
OL,13,Fmore than died the year before that.
OL,15,FIn the south of Scotland, however, the
OL,16,Fpicture is one of improvement. A dozen
OL,17,Fpeople died in Dumfries and Galloway,
OL,18,Fcompared to 37 in 2022. In the
OL,19,FScottish Borders, 11 people died, two
OL,20,Ffewer than the total number recorded
OL,21,Fthe year before.
