OL,4,Csouth of Scotland as national numbers
OL,5,Crise
OL,7,FGraeme Callander, a policy lead for
OL,8,Fthe charity, said: "I think what we do
OL,9,Fknow is that Scotland has real issues
OL,10,Fin terms of poverty, deprivation and
OL,11,Fthose are some of the key drivers to
OL,12,Fdrug related deaths and harms.
OL,14,F"Also in recent years we've seen
OL,15,Fcontaminated drugs enter the supply in
OL,16,FScotland," he added.
OL,18,FWhilst opioids, such as heroin, remain
OL,19,Fthe biggest cause of deaths, figures
OL,20,Frelated to other drugs, including
OL,21,Fcocaine, are rising.
